BT /F2 11 Tf 54 716.0 Td (Page 22) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (So here's what Cumulus wants you to know, little reader:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (It's okay to cry. It's okay to feel sad, or angry, or scared, or overwhelmed.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (Those feelings are not weakness   they are rain. And rain makes things grow.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (Don't hold everything in until you feel like you're going to burst. Let it out. Cry if you) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (need to. Talk about it. Express it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td (After every storm, the sky is clearer. After every cry, your heart is lighter. That's just) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td (how it works.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 582.4 Td ([Illustration: A child reading this book, perhaps with tears in their eyes, realizing it's) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568.4 Td (okay to feel and express emotions, a gentle and validating final image with a rainbow) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 554.4 Td (after rain]) Tj ET
endstream
